<!doctype html>
<html class="md-perspective">
<head>
	<meta name="robots" content="noindex">
	<title>QRPass</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/style.css">
</head>
<body>

	<div class="md-modal md-effect" id="modal-1">
		<div class="md-content">
            <button class="md-close" onclick="hideModal(1)">&#xea0f;</button>
			<button id="copy-button-userName">Copy username to Clipboard</button><br>
			<button id="copy-button-password">Copy password to Clipboard</button><br>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="md-overlay"></div>

    <div class="md-modal md-effect" id="modal-2">
        <div class="md-content">
            <button class="md-close" onclick="hideModal(2)">&#xea0f;</button>
            <h2>General note</h2>

            <p>The application works as KeePass2Android plugin and allows user to send credintials securely
                between KeePass2Android and browser using QRCode and server assistance as medium for exchanging
                encryption secrets and encrypted data</p>

            <p>All communication is secured with RSA encryption and random generated secure key exchanged by QR Code.
                There are plans to switch RSA with some asymetric encryption algorithm to hinder MITM attacks</p>

            <h2>Alpha note</h2>

            <p>The app is still in early alpha/development stage, so please forgive any incoviniences in usage.</p>

            <h2>Quick start</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Download and install <a href="/apk/android.apk">APK</a><br/>
                    You will have to allow device to install unsigned applications, since this release is highly
                    unofficial and unsigned at the moment
                </li>
                <li>Enable plugin in KeePass2Android settings.</li>
                <li>Open some user credintials entry and select to use it with QRPass in menu</li>
                <li>Scan QRcode from your browser</li>
                <li>You should receive username and password in your browser</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Special thanks to:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://code.google.com/p/crypto-js/">CryptoJS</a> - for cryptographic library</li>
                <li><a href="https://code.google.com/p/zeroclipboard/">ZeroClipboard</a> - for copy/paste flash library</li>
                <li><a href="https://nodejs.org/">Nods.js</a> - for... Node.JS</li>
                <li><a href="http://expressjs.com/">Express.js</a> - for... Express.JS</li>
                <li><a href="http://socket.io/">Socket.IO</a> - for super easy websocket abstraction</li>
                <li><a href="https://icomoon.io/">IcoMoon</a> - for super easy icon-font manager and such fonts library</li>
                <li><a href="https://github.com/davidshimjs/qrcodejs">davidshimjs</a> - for qrcode generation js library</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="md-overlay"></div>

    <div class="container" id="container">
		<div class="qrcode-wrap">
			<div class="qrcode qrcode-hide" id="qrcode">
                <a href="/apk/android.apk" class="icon-android">&#xeac1;</a>
                <button class="help_btn" onclick="showModal(2)">?</button>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

